                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">if Kandymann posted this info elsewhere on theRunes, I missed it
<br />

<br />
posted 09/15
<br />
<a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=enchanterbalance&message.id=1820" target="_blank">http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=enchanterbalance&message.id=1820</a>
<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Okey doke folks,
<br />
 
<br />
We feel that charm as it stood when used in pre-omens content had a disparity in its risk vs. reward.  Rather than adjust charm overall to reduce the amount of damage all charmed pets do even more, we made changes to the NPCs in the new zones only.  We also made more NPCs overall charmable to provide more variety and fun for the enchanter.   This is not a nerf.  The way charm works has not been changed one bit.  The way the new NPCs react when charmed has been modified so that we no longer have issues of charmed mobs doing the DPS of several rogues.  
<br />

<br />
Brenlo Bixiebopper
<br />
Community Relations Manager</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=81508" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Nadia </a> E70.895/BS 5.64khp 7.55km ft20
