                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Kandmyann,
<br />

<br />
Since you are in communication with Brenlo please relay this to him.
<br />

<br />
Now the dps is similar to a rogue backstabbing, a necro dotting, a mage pet. There is nothing wrong with that.
<br />

<br />
However, unlike a rogue's backstab, a necro's dot on a mob, or a mage's pet, a charmed mob will attempt to kill the enchanter and his/her group ever 6 seconds to 7.5 minutes and will take up to 1/3 of the experience.  
<br />

<br />
If the dps is the same, the risk should be the same: none.  If the dps is the same: the experience should be the same.
<br />

<br />
Mobs with a seperate damage table should follow the same rules as any other pet to balance risk versus reward.  Obviously the solution won't be that simple, however, the net result should be the same.
<br />

<br />
There is no reason for me to charm in a group when I can do the same damage nuking without endangering my group and lessening its experience. 
<br />

<br />
Charm most definitely is broken in OoW.  The mob changes broke it.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=554032" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.ageofmages.com/images/Fairy-sig.gif" border="0" /></a>
