                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My first response to this was going to be one word: "unacceptable." But I realize that isn't productive...
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Kandyman</span>, please bring one thing to them for contemplation:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-size: 14px; line-height: normal">When OoW was planned and even when it went to beta we had been given two <span style="font-style: italic">pre-nerf</span> charm upgrades as part of the package that was to balance us with other classes. Merely a week before release, those charm abilities were severly nerfed in a variety of ways that, we as a community, believe will render them all but useless. Meanwhile <span style="font-style: italic">nothing</span> was given us in compensation for this. In short, we find ourselves in a class balance situation where the very thing that was to make us on par with the other 10 classes has been totally removed leaving us with a huge hole in our level 66-70 ability set. Whether it is charm or something else - something new.. We need <span style="font-style: italic">some</span> sort of powerful compensation to allow our class to continue to 1. be on par with the others and 2. improve and enjoy levels 66-70. As it stands now, this nerf has left our class' power nearly stagnant or even diminished relative to when level 65 was the norm while simultaneously upgrading the others to a new, level 70 base. Can you see how this could quickly become a recipee for disaster for our class?</span></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=361216" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ariu <span style="font-style: italic">stop destroying my class damnit!</span> Vil''''Aki &lt;Heroes&gt;</a>
<br />
