Pre-OOW
<br />

<br />
I can charm mobs within 5 levels of my level (i.e. no exp penalty) and get good exp as a result.  I can also charm an unhasted mob (which I have often done when I consider the risk of charm break to be too high) and that mob has a good chance of beating its opponent.
<br />

<br />
With OOW
<br />

<br />
At level 70, the mobs that I can charm that are within 5 levels of my own is very slim.  In future expansions when you raise the level cap to level 75, there will be none.  By level 100, everything will be green that can be charmed in old zones.  In the end, you have nerfed our charm abilities, and made the skill next to useless.  To suggest that this is not a nerf makes you sound like a politician.  (:</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
